,Recommended,298600,13775614,"Posted: 1 January, 2015",all,Orange Enigma,"Lovely Planet lives up to its name and is truly a lovely game. It reminds me of Super Meat Boy in the sense that it encourages replaying until you ace a level, and is not as frustrating as it may seem due to the great soundtrack that continues to play through deaths, quick restarts, and the real sense of accomplishment one will get once they beat a level that has been the bane of their play. I have not finished it yet, and have only finished 2 out of 5 worlds, but I am sure I will come back again and again when I need something relaxing, yet challenging to play. Which is a good point to bring up. Lovely Planet is a very relaxing game. The cutesy pastel aesthetic is one that really sets it apart from other FPS style games and combined the soundtrack backing it, makes for an almost meditative experience. Sure, there will be some moments where you feel frustrated, but every death of mine (and there are many) has felt like it is my fault. Not the game's. All in all, I can't believe this is only 5 dollars. It is a wonderful experience. One that I feel many will enjoy. If you are easily frustrated, I would say stay away, but if you are curious, go for it. I think fans of the ""just one more try"" games will love this. I did."
