76561198045311771,Recommended,298600,11569403,"Posted: 5 August, 2014",all,Kimmy B,"The most amazing fps (first person shooter) to this date that I have ever played.If you are looking for a military shooter, it's not this.If you are looking for a multiplayer game to shoot your friends, it's not this.Who ever is left and is wondering what lovely planet is. The answer is that it is the most hardcore intense shooter ever created and one of the most colorful and cheerful atmospheres I have ever had the privledge to play in.So what, I could just boot up TF2 and go to some unofficial server and do the same thing but with my little pony.Well, If you are not a brony, (or are) this game is just as effervescent.Ok so what if it is cute. You said it was the ""most hardcore intense shooter ever"".In most military/hardcore shooters there is no hud (heads up display). This lack of a retical or something to guess where your bullets will go adds a unique level of challenge to this fps.Whoopdedoo theres no hud, that all you got.Well no actually, this game is timed and the goal is to get 3 stars.Stars?Yes, the stars are awarded upon three criteria. First that you completed the level (blue star). Second that you did it in a reasonable time (green star). Third that you had perfect accuracy (yellow star), which can be dificult considering that you have no retical to aim with.Ok there is nothing left to do after I finish all three stars?Wrong, if you by some arcane magic manage to finish all of the levels with three stars you can shoot for the world record on the levels.And after that?Ascend to godhood.I whole heartedly recomend this game."
