,Not Recommended,298600,12296673,"Posted: 29 September, 2014",all,owlyoop cockatoo,"It's okay. Nowhere near as fun as quake live's race gamemode. It's kind of different from that, but with less depth, with the former being about movement+precision aiming (rocket jumps etc.) and this game being ONLY about precision aiming. The movement in this game is not very good. Walking down a slope will just make you instantly slide down it, way faster than you floating down from jumping.I don't know why a game entirely about precision aiming has no crosshair. Just because the projectiles inherit momentum doesn't make a crosshair useless. All removing the crosshair does is add guesswork to the game, which is stupid when most levels have very small frame windows in which to shoot homing projectiles. The stupidity multiplies whenever said projectiles are waiting for you in front of a teleporter exit.That being said I think most people could find enjoyment out of the first 3 worlds since their less cheesy and actually give you some freedom of how you complete the levels. The swamp (4th world) levels are filled with guess-working tiny windows of opportunity, and guessing where the falling apples(?) are going to be when your screen is entirely fog and you have no depth perception. Mountain (5th world) has even more homing missile spam in-front of you as you leave a teleporter. Not very fun or exciting, but the main point of saying all of this is that there's no freedom in how you execute these things. There's no discovery on what the most optimal route is, or how to do it.The music is alright. The visuals are alright but they feel a bit lazy. They're not bad and their artistic talent is still there,  it just looks like the developers could do better."
