,Recommended,298600,11512706,"Posted: 1 August, 2014",all,BaconJets,"This game needs more exposure. It's an addictive FPS where the objective is to shoot every baddie in the level and complete it as fast as possible all while bunny hopping across the treacherous terrain like a maniac. The levels typically can be completed in about 20 seconds and this is where the game taps into the same nerve for efficiency as Super Meat Boy, where you'll complete a level and say ""I didn't do that well enough"" and do it again. You'll be rated on both time of completion and accuracy and the game continuously brings in bombastic, insane mechanics such as apples that launch into the air and cause an instant fail if they aren't shot before reaching the ground. It's brutal in difficulty as everything is a one hit kill, but entirely fair.Counteracting the absolute insanity of flying apples and projectiles is the aesthetic. It seems indie devs are starting to move onto turning the low poly graphics of the 90s into a visual style much in the same way as 16 and 8 bit graphics have been. The closest game I can compare this to visually is the Katamari series. Everything has a quirky, colourful aesthetic to it with delightful bouncy music by Bo En. This is a world made out of origami floating inside a PS1 while you're on LSD and it's absolutely amazing. Best of all, it will run on pretty much anything.This game is extremely cheap and if you're a fan of FPS games and want something different, you'd be a fool for not picking this up."
