,Recommended,298600,16874553,"Posted: 4 July, 2015",all,Wong,"[Skip to the verdict if you want a short summary]What is lovely planet?Lovely planet is a twitch first person shooter rage game platformer thing. In the game you traverse through different colourful levels, trying to kill alll enemies, not miss any shots and beat your time. It may sound easy but believe me when I sayit's not...there will be many obstacles alog the way.The love and the hateIf you rage easily in games dont get this, okay? Most of the time you will be repeating the same stage time after time again because you made stupid mistakes. The other portion of the time you will be smashing your keyboard and screaming words that you didnt even know you could say. But: Im not saying thats a bad thing because its not. It adds to playtime and it make winning a level feel very rewarding.The two most amazing aspects of this game for me are the artstyle and soundtrack. It really makes me chuckle when I realise Iv been screaming at a bunch of colourful polygons and a happy japenese tune. They both remind me alot of Japan and I think thats what they were going for considering the random japenese writing everywhere. The artstyle consists of minimilistic colourful blobs that make it easy to tell enemies and ground apart with their colours that stand out. The music in itself makes the game. The music is a nice upbeat happy track which makes you forget about all your troubles and just stand and listen. It is so happy I wonder how it could be played over the top of such an evil game! In fact I am listening to it while reading this review and it makes me not want to list a bad point about the game!The gameplay in this game is the usual. Considering that it is mainly concentrated on platforming and twitch shooting which I hate it still felt smooth and I felt as if my shots were hitting when they should. The gun felt nice although you couldnt change what gun you had which I thought would of been cool although it probably would of messed up the leaderboards for speedrunners. So I think this game could use a bit more variety to make it a bit more intresting and unique.Something this game is missing is a story which although twitch shooters dont normally have a story I think that super meat boy pulled of a pretty nice story so this could probably do it to! I felt as if that made the world I ran through feel empty and without meaning. Also I think a story would of made me want to progress a bit further into the game whereas right now Iv given up because Iv been stuck for an hour. Also It might add to the replayability.The verdictLovely planet is a rage inducing twitch shooter with platforming aspects. Its soundtrack and world makes up for the lack of story. Beware you may break something.Love+Soundtrack+Graphics+Gameplay+Long playtimeHate-No story-Rage-Variety6.5/10Thank you for reading, if you enjoyed dont forget to:Join my curator group!Visit my website!Watch me on youtube!"
