76561198075457818,Recommended,298600,11523178,"Posted: 2 August, 2014",all,orbajo,"For 6 bucks, or 5 on sale right now, you really can't get more bang for your buck. I've already put 5 hours into this game and barely gotten halfway through it. What's the best way to describe it? An FPS Puzzle/speedrun game? This is a game about shooting weird square enemies and other crazy looking stuff in the face with precision and speed, all the while incorporating platforming and twitch reflexes. And you do this listening to one of the greatest videogame soundtracks I've heard in years, it's very reminiscent of Katamari Damacy. In fact, the aesthetic of this game has already been compared to Katamari Damacy many times, and I totally agree with it.It's weird, it's quirky, it's challenging as hell and it will punish you for the slightest mistake if you're going for all the stars in a certain level, but you'll also just keep coming back. This is 'just one more try' in it's purest form. The game appears to have about 100 levels and has a pretty balanced learning curve; if you're a perfectionist, getting all the stars in this game is gonna take quite some time.I have to say when I saw video of someone playing this it didn't blow me away. This is DEFINITELY the type of game you have to play for yourself to see what's so great about it. It's bliss. When you finally get the perfect run, it's like entering a zen state. You'll just have to fight through many many many restarts and cursing at the game to get there. But trust me, it's worth it.One of the best indie games to come out in a long time."
