76561198017167209,Recommended,298600,11628483,"Posted: 10 August, 2014",all,daedremes,"This is -- beyond a reasonable doubt -- a hidden treasure among video games.  I haven't been this engaged and had this much fun with a video game in a long time.  It's very challenging while not being relentless.  As far as FPS games go, it's pretty different from anything else out there.  The goal of each level is to shoot all the enemies (and certain objects) that are strategically placed throughout the course all in one go.  There are no checkpoints.  If you die, you start the level over.  Completing the level with proficient time and gun accuracy awards you with an extra star.  The game's difficulty increases at a moderate pace and each level offers a unique challenge.  New game mechanics are thrown in at certain points along with new enemies.  You may get stuck on a level now and then but you don't feel hopeless.  You learn from each failure and feel like you are improving as a player.  The gameplay is complimented by the visuals which manage to be quirky and charming all while being extremely simple.  The music fits right along with the art style with an upbeat tempo that puts you in a good mood.Most AAA titles these days have not given me the amount of enjoyment I've gotten from this game.  And those games cost roughly 5 to 10 times more than this one!  I honestly would have spent 20 dollars for this game. It's a steal for the price.Try this game.  It's hard no to fall in love with it."
