,Recommended,298600,11522424,"Posted: 2 August, 2014",all,DIPE,"Lovely Planet has far more depth behind it than its flat, colorful palette suggests. An FPS dedicated more towards movement than killing, the objective is to get to the end of each stage as quickly as possible while shooting all the baddies with your star gun, avoiding all the red things that could kill you and more. There's a pretty clear path through each stage yet it seems each (if not all) have easily missed shortcuts and other tricks that shave seconds off each run. Its frantic, restart-as-soon-as-you-miss mechanics works so well in reinforcing the drive to improve your time. Each group of stages introduces new mechanics gradually but in a way that challenges without becoming frustrating. Of course, these mechanics compound in the later stages becoming downright sadistic at points.I'm disappointed by the lack of leaderboards as the world record just doesn't give nearly enough motivation to improve. The movement is also a bit floaty and takes some getting used to if you're more familar with Source movement but it's consistent throughout.Totally worth the $6."
