,Recommended,298600,15937201,"Posted: 22 May, 2015",all,Macheti,"I didn't exactly know what to expect when I first played this game, and initially it looked like an interesting time-killer when I was bored and needed to play something different. On the surface, this game begins as a fun, cute platforming FPS in which you have to reach the finish pole while also eliminating every enemy in the level, these enemies being red blobs of various shapes. Some of these enemies shoot bullets which you can parry by shooting with your own gun. Wanting to get all the achievements, I had to get 3 stars on every level, one for finishing, one for finishing quickly, and one for 100% accuracy. This was an enjoyable challenge because it kept things tense in the first few worlds as I had to aim my shots carefully and be hasty.The last 2 worlds, Swamp and Mountains, were a whole different story however. Homing bullets were introduced, ones that you must shoot or death is basically guaranteed. Levels became misty, and homing bullets started flying out of nowhere. Bombs that are launched and must be shot before they hit the ground or you are killed instantly involve having to gauge where the bomb will be at a certain time and shooting at that spot, which is more fun than it sounds. With all these elements combined, eventually, the game turned into one of the hardest FPS/platforming experiences I've had, at least in order to get 3 stars in every level. Due to a requirement of 100% accuracy, every shot had to count, and no excess shots were allowed. After hours of memorising and practice, I would have to progress through the level, flicking and swiping to the next target, doing 90 and 180 turns constantly in order to shoot the various obstacles in my way. Despite all this difficulty, when you finally reach that finish pole with 100% accuracy, it makes you feel like some action movie star or an aim-botter of some kind :P. While torturing and rage-inducing, the rewarding experience of succeeding in this way is unmatched, and the main reason why I recommend this game, and what makes it so enjoyable.There are also a number of secrets in the game, which are fun to look for and find, especially the fabled ""Planet Shrine"" secret which is an elusive one and may require some research to be discovered.Overall, much better than it seems on the surface, and should be played and 3 starred until the end for maximum enjoyment.10/10"
